               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480918-name-864" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-864" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-864" type="surname" value="WEARING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-864" type="given" value="JONATHAN"></interp>JONATHAN WEARING</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at George-terrace, New Kent-road. On Thursday morning, about two o'clock, I met the prisoner and another, about ten yards from Waterloo-bridge—they wished me to pay for their going over—I refused, but just as I was paying my fare they passed me, and I paid for them—they requested me to go up Earl-street with them—I refused—they hustled me; I felt a jerk, and missed my watch from my waistcoat-pocket—the prisoner ran—two men, who I had observed before, came up squaring at me, and said, "You are a pretty fellow to have connection with a female in a public thoroughfare," and prevented my following her—I escaped, and followed her—I turned a corner, and found her in charge—she gave me my watch—this is it (<hi rend="italic">produced.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. METCALFE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Where had you been? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> To Tottenham Court-road.</p>
